  "text": "The CRD validation schema to OpenAPI publishing chain in Kubernetes operates as follows:\n\n1. **CRD Validation Schema Definition** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apis/apiextensions/v1/types.go): CustomResourceDefinition objects contain CustomResourceValidation in their spec.Versions[].Schema field. CustomResourceValidation includes an OpenAPIV3Schema field of type JSONSchemaProps that defines the validation schema for custom resources.\n\n2. **Structural Schema Extraction** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/schema/convert.go): The NewStructural function (line 42) converts the JSONSchemaProps validation schema into an internal Structural representation. This function extracts structure-defining fields (type, properties, items, additionalProperties) while preserving validation constraints (format, pattern, minimum/maximum, etc.) in the ValueValidation field.\n\n3. **Structural Schema Definition** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/schema/structural.go): The Structural type represents the extracted schema with fields for Generic (type info), Extensions (Kubernetes vendor extensions like x-kubernetes-preserve-unknown-fields), ValidationExtensions (x-kubernetes-validations), and ValueValidation (constraint fields).\n\n4. **OpenAPI v3 Schema Conversion** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/schema/kubeopenapi.go): The ToKubeOpenAPI method on Structural (line 24) converts the internal representation into kube-openapi's spec.Schema format, which is OpenAPI v3 compatible. This method recursively converts properties, items, additionalProperties, and applies all validation and extension fields.\n\n5. **CRD to OpenAPI V3 Builder** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/controller/openapi/builder/builder.go): The BuildOpenAPIV3 function (line 194) orchestrates the end-to-end conversion. It calls generateBuilder which extracts the schema, converts it to Structural via NewStructural, and then uses builder3.BuildOpenAPISpecFromRoutes to create complete OpenAPI v3 specifications including all API endpoints and models.\n\n6. **OpenAPI V3 Controller** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/controller/openapiv3/controller.go): The Controller watches CustomResourceDefinition resources. When CRDs are added/updated/deleted, it calls buildV3Spec (line 237) which invokes BuildOpenAPIV3. The resulting spec is stored in specsByGVandName and updateGroupVersion (line 192) merges specs and publishes them via the OpenAPIService.\n\n7. **API Server OpenAPI Routes** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/routes/openapi.go): The OpenAPI type's InstallV3 method (line 53) registers the /openapi/v3 endpoint on the API server. The openAPIV3Service.UpdateGroupVersion call (line 74) publishes the merged OpenAPI v3 specs for each group/version, making CRD schemas available via the Kubernetes API server's OpenAPI discovery endpoint.\n\n8. **OpenAPI Endpoint Handler** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/openapi/openapi.go): This package contains utilities like GetOperationIDAndTags that help format OpenAPI operation definitions from API routes, supporting the proper serialization of CRD-based resources in the OpenAPI spec."
